 Introduction
 ------------

  Many different small games and graphical
  effects in a window, wich is best served
  with music.
  Also includes some creative utilities.
  
  The whole thing started when I got one
  pixel to bounce in a window. :)

 
 Requirements
 ------------

  -An aga or cgx 68k Amiga with workbench,
   or workbench replacement.

  -Any kind of music.
   The 'watchNplay.ns' exe does not interfere with
   sound output.
    Ok, it doesnt NEED music.. but it adds
   a whole lot to the atmosphere of the graphical effects.

  -Fat agnus, or Paula sound chips
   for the Sound stuff.

  
 Installation
 ------------

  keep everything where it is
  when extracted, and it is ok.

  You can run watchNplay by CLI or WB.
  

 Features
 --------

  + Is in a window on the workbench
    and therefore multitasks
  + Uses random variable generation to
    avoid the same over and over again.
  + Changes menu after which mode is on.
  + Has many options for certain modes
    that strenghtens durability.
  + Doesn't need to obtain pens.
    Searches for adequate colors instead.
  + Every mode will stay as you left them
    if you switch to another one. That way
    you can continue a game of <Poker>
    after you, for instance, have looked at
    <Picture> a while.
  + So much more and more depending on the mode!


 Modes
 -----

  Every mode has its own option set,
  and only the options of the running
  mode will be shown.
   modes or options with "UC!" markings
  are Under Construction, and I reccomend
  you not to select them because they are
  incomplete and almost certainly contain bugs.
   But if you do, you are welcome to give me
  suggestions about it.

 Wierd chars reference:

-  = One or more suboptions for the option above.
*  = An independent switch set in the current menu.
     when one is enabled, all others are not.
x# = # for a number. x4 means that your score gained
     in a game are multiplied by 4 ingame or at gameover.


 I will skip modes under construction. UC! markings.



