:utility modes:

 

  Soundscool
  **********

   play with atoms pushing eachother to your ear. (sound)
    
   You edit the main window with your mouse
   What you draw is a piece of wave wich is
   played from left to right.

   The slide edit option should be used first,
   as it makes it easy to make a wave.
   You can select <on center> and <-place at start>
   to create the sound from start to end.

   Soundscool is handy to make small samples for games.
 

    WARNING!

    The sound can get noisy,
    so I dont reccomend listening to much
    to a looping sound,
    since you will get a little wierd afterwards. ;)

  



